Round 2 Code Changes
====================

This file summarizes the code changes that were applied for the multivariate / heterogeneous feature forecasting round.

1) 5_code_base/optimized/power_models/common.py
- Added FEATURE_PROFILES for baseline, temporal, graph, patch, and xgboost feature layouts.
- Added time context features, auxiliary column selection, and build_feature_matrix().
- Extended make_dataset_bundle() with feature_profile selection.
- Expanded compute_metrics() to return MAE, RMSE, SMAPE, WAPE, and R2.
- Kept physics_postprocess() for bounded post-processing.

2) 5_code_base/optimized/power_models/xgboost_model.py
- Switched to feature_profile="xgboost".
- Reduced the sequence length and simplified XGBoost hyperparameters for runtime stability.
- Added GPU-aware fitting with CPU fallback.

3) 5_code_base/optimized/power_models/timesnet_model.py
- Switched to feature_profile="temporal".
- Kept the TimesNetLite backbone but adjusted device selection and training settings.
- Preserved physics-aware penalty and post-processing.

4) 5_code_base/optimized/power_models/mtgnn_model.py
- Switched to feature_profile="graph".
- Kept correlation-based adjacency construction and physics-aware training.
- Updated the optimized hidden dimension and device selection.

5) 5_code_base/optimized/power_models/patchtst_model.py
- Added PatchTSTLite with patch tokenization, positional embedding, and a Transformer encoder.
- Switched to feature_profile="patch".
- Added a dedicated train_eval_patchtst() path with physics-aware training.

6) 6_experiment_execution/pipeline/run_round_fixed_pipeline.py
- Expanded the evaluation pipeline from three models to four models by adding PatchTST.
- Kept baseline vs optimized comparisons for XGBoost, TimesNet, MTGNN, and PatchTST.
- Limited evaluation to tail(3000) rows to keep the round execution stable.
- Exported round_fixed_metrics.json and FINAL_RESEARCH_REPORT_FIXED_ROUND.md.

7) 2_agent_system/1_research_manager/run.py
- Added round archive handling via _round_archive_dir() and _write_round_archive().
- Added round_summary.md generation and standardized round artifact naming.
- Reduced the demo slice to tail(1500) for faster validation.

8) .vscode/tasks.json
- Kept the round workflow tasks for the second round.

9) tools/run_round2.cmd
- Added a local Windows wrapper that launches the round-2 research flow and redirects the execution log to report/round2_run.log.
